Subject: [PATCH 7/7] Fix prompt classifier failing on slash-prefixed prompts

Upstream issue: danielmiessler/Personal_AI_Infrastructure#1158

`hooks/PromptProcessing.hook.ts` runs the Sonnet mode/tier classifier on
every UserPromptSubmit via the `claude --print` subprocess in
`PAI/TOOLS/Inference.ts`. When the user prompt starts with "/" (any
slash-command — /interview, /loop, /migrate, etc.), `claude --print`
reads stdin starting with "/" as a CLI slash-command and returns
`Unknown command: /<X>`. The classifier's JSON parse fails. The
fail-safe path then writes `MODE: ALGORITHM | TIER: E3 | REASON:
inference failed | SOURCE: fail-safe` into additionalContext.

User-visible symptom: every "/"-prefixed prompt that reaches the
classifier escalates to ALGORITHM E3 regardless of the actual
workflow's complexity. Cosmetic noise, telemetry pollution, and
occasional unwanted ceremony.

Fix: wrap leading-"/" prompts as `User invoked: <prompt>` before
sending to the classifier. The classifier still sees the actual prompt
text after the prefix and produces the right MODE/TIER for the
underlying intent. Verbatim from the upstream issue's proposed fix
(also tested locally by the reporter).

File touched (line in upstream PAI v5.0.0):

  Releases/v5.0.0/.claude/hooks/PromptProcessing.hook.ts                :926-931

Hunks generated via `diff -u` against the extracted upstream tarball
(/nix/store/zm296ivyw3qg1a2fm4aa7ns10f3ldy4c-v5.0.0.tar.gz). No
hand-counted @@ headers (lesson from patch 0005 Changelog
2026-05-02T17:35:00Z).
---
--- a/Releases/v5.0.0/.claude/hooks/PromptProcessing.hook.ts
+++ b/Releases/v5.0.0/.claude/hooks/PromptProcessing.hook.ts
@@ -924,11 +924,16 @@
     console.error('[PromptProcessing] Running inference (tab title' + (isFirstPrompt ? ' + session name)...' : ')...'));
 
     const cleanPrompt = prompt.replace(/<[^>]*>/g, ' ').replace(/\s+/g, ' ').trim().slice(0, 1000);
+    // Wrap leading-`/` so `claude --print` doesn't read it as a CLI slash-command
+    // (which would return "Unknown command: /X" and fail JSON parse → E3 fail-safe).
+    const safePrompt = cleanPrompt.startsWith('/')
+      ? `User invoked: ${cleanPrompt}`
+      : cleanPrompt;
     // Naming is permanent and first-prompt-only; exclude Assistant turns so Algorithm scaffolding
     // (phase headers, agent names, SUMMARY lines) cannot contaminate the session name. Tab-title
     // inference on later prompts keeps Assistant context for "continue with X" style follow-ups.
     const context = getRecentContext(data.transcript_path, 6, !isFirstPrompt);
-    const userPrompt = context ? `CONTEXT:\n${context}\n\nCURRENT MESSAGE:\n${cleanPrompt}` : cleanPrompt;
+    const userPrompt = context ? `CONTEXT:\n${context}\n\nCURRENT MESSAGE:\n${safePrompt}` : safePrompt;
 
     const inferenceStart = Date.now();
     try {
